---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Development Roadmap - TunnelForge Documentation">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Development Roadmap</h1>
    <p>Our vision and timeline for TunnelForge's evolution and feature development.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <section class="overview">
      <h2>Roadmap Overview</h2>
      <p>This roadmap outlines our development priorities, feature milestones, and long-term vision for TunnelForge. We focus on user needs, technical excellence, and community-driven development.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="current-quarter">
      <h2>Q1 2025 - Foundation & Core Features</h2>
      
      <h3>Completed âœ…</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Core Terminal Sharing</strong> - Basic session management and web interface</li>
        <li><strong>Cross-Platform Support</strong> - macOS, Linux, and web browser support</li>
        <li><strong>Authentication System</strong> - Multiple auth methods and security</li>
        <li><strong>Documentation Site</strong> - Comprehensive docs with Astro and Svelte</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>In Progress ðŸ”„</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance Optimization</strong> - Terminal rendering improvements</li>
        <li><strong>Mobile Web Interface</strong> - Responsive design for mobile devices</li>
        <li><strong>Error Handling</strong> - Comprehensive error management</li>
        <li><strong>Testing Infrastructure</strong> - Automated testing setup</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="q2-2025">
      <h2>Q2 2025 - Enhanced User Experience</h2>
      
      <h3>Planned Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Advanced Session Management</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Session templates and presets</li>
            <li>Automated session recovery</li>
            <li>Session sharing with permissions</li>
            <li>Collaborative editing modes</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Enhanced Web Interface</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Customizable themes and layouts</li>
            <li>Advanced terminal customization</li>
            <li>Keyboard shortcut management</li>
            <li>Accessibility improvements</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Mobile Applications</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Native iOS app development</li>
            <li>Android app planning</li>
            <li>Mobile-optimized workflows</li>
            <li>Push notifications</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="q3-2025">
      <h2>Q3 2025 - Collaboration & Enterprise</h2>
      
      <h3>Team Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>User Management</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Role-based access control</li>
            <li>Team organization</li>
            <li>Audit logging</li>
            <li>SSO integration</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Advanced Sharing</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Read-only sharing modes</li>
            <li>Session recording and playback</li>
            <li>Comment and annotation system</li>
            <li>Integration with chat platforms</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="q4-2025">
      <h2>Q4 2025 - Platform & Ecosystem</h2>
      
      <h3>Platform Expansion</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Plugin System</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Plugin architecture design</li>
            <li>Developer SDK</li>
            <li>Plugin marketplace</li>
            <li>Custom integrations</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>API & Integrations</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>REST API v2</li>
            <li>GraphQL support</li>
            <li>Webhook system</li>
            <li>Third-party integrations</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="long-term">
      <h2>2026+ - Future Vision</h2>
      
      <h3>Advanced Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>AI Integration</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Intelligent command suggestions</li>
            <li>Automated troubleshooting</li>
            <li>Smart session management</li>
            <li>Predictive analytics</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Cloud Platform</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Hosted TunnelForge instances</li>
            <li>Multi-tenant architecture</li>
            <li>Global edge deployment</li>
            <li>Enterprise features</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Advanced Terminal</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>GPU-accelerated rendering</li>
            <li>Custom terminal protocols</li>
            <li>Advanced input methods</li>
            <li>Resource monitoring</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Workflow Automation</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Macro recording and playback</li>
        <li>Scheduled tasks</li>
        <li>Webhook triggers</li>
        <li>API automation</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="technical-debt">
      <h2>Technical Debt & Maintenance</h2>
      
      <h3>Ongoing Improvements</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Increase test coverage to 90%+</li>
        <li>Automated performance regression testing</li>
        <li>Security vulnerability scanning</li>
        <li>Dependency updates automation</li>
        <li>Documentation generation from code</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Code Quality</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>TypeScript strict mode everywhere</li>
        <li>Consistent error handling patterns</li>
        <li>Comprehensive API documentation</li>
        <li>Example applications and tutorials</li>
        <li>Video documentation</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="success-metrics">
      <h2>Success Metrics</h2>
      
      <h3>Technical KPIs</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance</strong>: P99 latency &lt; 100ms</li>
        <li><strong>Reliability</strong>: 99.99% uptime</li>
        <li><strong>Quality</strong>: &lt;1 critical bug per release</li>
        <li><strong>Security</strong>: 0 security incidents</li>
        <li><strong>Testing</strong>: &gt;90% code coverage</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>User KPIs</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Adoption</strong>: 50,000+ monthly active users</li>
        <li><strong>Retention</strong>: 70% 30-day retention</li>
        <li><strong>Satisfaction</strong>: NPS &gt; 60</li>
        <li><strong>Community</strong>: 5,000+ Discord members</li>
        <li><strong>Contributors</strong>: 100+ open source contributors</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="research-development">
      <h2>Research & Development</h2>
      
      <h3>Experimental Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>WebAssembly Terminal</strong>: Run terminal emulation in WASM</li>
        <li><strong>Distributed Sessions</strong>: Session migration between servers</li>
        <li><strong>Blockchain Integration</strong>: Decentralized session storage</li>
        <li><strong>AR/VR Support</strong>: Terminal in virtual reality</li>
        <li><strong>Voice Control</strong>: Natural language terminal commands</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Technology Evaluation</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Rust Rewrite</strong>: Evaluate full Rust implementation</li>
        <li><strong>QUIC Protocol</strong>: Replace WebSocket with QUIC</li>
        <li><strong>WebTransport</strong>: Next-gen web protocol adoption</li>
        <li><strong>WebGPU</strong>: GPU-accelerated terminal rendering</li>
        <li><strong>Machine Learning</strong>: Intelligent command completion</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="community">
      <h2>Community & Open Source</h2>
      
      <h3>Engagement Strategy</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Monthly community calls</li>
        <li>Quarterly hackathons</li>
        <li>Bug bounty program</li>
        <li>Conference presentations</li>
        <li>Technical blog posts</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Contribution Areas</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Documentation improvements</li>
        <li>Translation and localization</li>
        <li>Plugin development</li>
        <li>Testing and QA</li>
        <li>Security research</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <div class="next-steps">
      <h2>Get Involved</h2>
      <p>Join our <a href="https://discord.gg/3Ub3EUwrcR" target="_blank">Discord</a> to participate in roadmap discussions and planning. This roadmap is a living document updated quarterly based on user feedback and technical discoveries.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #e5e7eb;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    color: #1f2937;
  }

  .page-header p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: #6b7280;
  }

  .content section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .content h2 {
    color: #1f2937;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
  }

  .content h3 {
    color: #374151;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem 0;
  }

  ul, ol {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  a {
    color: #2563eb;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .next-steps {
    background-color: #eff6ff;
    border: 1px solid #bfdbfe;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .next-steps h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    color: #1e40af;
  }

  .next-steps p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: #1e40af;
  }
</style>
